    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>To Prevent More Strays</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Melanie Coronetz letter on Apr 26 article backs New York City bill to require spaying and neutering of dogs and cats adopted from shelters as well as those sold in pet stores</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I applaud the New York City Council's support of the bill to require the spaying and neutering of dogs and cats adopted from shelters as well as those sold in pet stores (news article, April 26). Most reputable breeders of pure-bred dogs, for example, will insist on spaying or neutering before they hand over the papers unless the animal is specifically sold as a show prospect. It's about time that pet stores were required to do the same.</p>
        <p>MELANIE CORONETZ  New York, April 26, 2000</p>
      </block>
